"12oz. bottle served in a can glass. Pours a hazy caramel hue with a loose, 1/4 inch, off-white head that quickly dissipates into a tight band around the shoulders. Nose expresses a hint of something spicy/fruity as well as grassy/herbal hops character. Taste consistent with nose; however, biscuity and caramel notes are the more prominent features in the flavor profile; whereas the spicy and earthy/herbal qualities come out at the finish. Mouthfeel is light in body with a lively carbonation that falls a little shy of crisp. Overall, a pretty drinkable ESB with a bit more character to the malt profile than I've come to associate with the style - this might explain the slightly higher abv."
