"Overall 3.5: Good tasting beer, but misses the mark by far in its attempt to be an English bitter. Too many bubbles (too much CO2 or bottle conditioning), not enough focus on the malt, and the hops...don't get me started on the hops. English bitters are known for their restrained and grassy British hops. There is nothing restrained or grassy about the hops in this beer. Again, this is a good beer, but it tastes nothing like an English bitter. This is simply an IPA in ESB's clothing."
